##The Passion and predicament of private donation in Hubei Province

China News Service, director, China Newsweek. Based in China, we focus on global charity and social issues, providing professional and rational reports and analyses with depth and temperature.

Delivering protection to the eye of the storm is no easy task

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Doctors at Wuhan Central Hospital tweeted for help, asking for donations from all walks of life. Photo: Screenshot via Weibo

On the evening of February 12, a doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital posted a request for help on his microblog.

The doctor, wearing a protective suit, told the camera that the medical N95 was gone, leaving him to wear an industrial mask, no medical shoe covers and a disposable garbage bag, while underneath his suit was a "thin sequestering garment. ".

"I hope you will do your best to make sure that the blood of the medical staff is not wasted. If you can donate some supplies, please do so. Let's not go to the battlefield naked and without armour. "

Turning off the camera, he went to ward rounds, where he had 34 new coronary patients waiting for him.

Over the past day, the appeal video has attracted more than 30,000 retweets and more than 5,000 comments. Many netizens want to donate their masks to the hospital, "Can I mail you three N95s? " "I have 25 American n95s. Can I use them? SF gives them to you. "

On February 13, the reporter called the relevant medical staff of the Wuhan Central Hospital to learn that the N95 medical mask was indeed gone. The medical staff used surgical masks to overlay the dust masks and industrial masks, doctors for help, "thin as CICADA, " the isolation collar is also not. In addition, when nurses take throat swabs from patients, they need to wear a mask to avoid infection, but no mask is currently available.

Front-line goods still have gap, the hospital appeals for social donation

This hospital is not the only one short of supplies.

On February 10, Wuhan First Hospital issued a public appeal for donations. The next day, the reporter learned from the hospital staff that the first hospital in Wuhan will receive more than 1000 new pneumonia patients on February 12. "At the moment there are 400 suits a day, and things are going to be tight when patients come in. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan First Hospital on February 10 issued a comprehensive material emergency notice

Wuhan Tianyou Hospital also released a list of items in short supply on February 5. February 10, the hospital staff said that the current shortage of protective clothing and not up to standard, they wear raincoats in protective clothing, wrapped in plastic wrap for protection.

In addition, Wuhan Children's Hospital, Wuhan Fourth Hospital and Wuhan Central Hospital on February 9, February 7 and February 6, respectively, issued a list of urgently needed materials, appeal for public donations.

This is the third time the front-line hospital has responded to the outbreak of the new coronavirus in Wuhan.

On January 23, the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, the Union Hospital and other eight hospitals issued a notice one after another to urgently solicit protective supplies from all sectors of society. That call made people aware of the extreme severity of the situation facing Hubei and triggered the first wave of civilian supplies to Hubei.

On January 30, Xiehe Hospital sent emergency medical aid again  Medical materials were not "in an emergency" , but "almost out" , which aroused public doubts about the efficiency of the Wuhan Red Cross Society in distributing materials. In addition to the questions, the alumni association, overseas Chinese groups and student groups again mobilized around the world to purchase supplies.

Zhong Nanshan estimates that the epidemic may have peaked in mid to late February and hopes to be over by April. In this protracted war, only the provinces to support Hubei Medical personnel close to 20,000 people, Hubei disposable medical protective supplies consumption is huge, the gap is still.

Cao Guangjing, vice governor of Hubei Province, said at a press conference on February 8 on "the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia" , at present, the supply of medical materials in Hubei Province is "a very tight and dynamic basic satisfaction, " he said, adding that "with the constant changes in the epidemic situation, the contradiction of shortage of some medical materials may also become prominent. ".

He cited the supply of protective clothing as an example. On February 7, the minimum demand for medical protective materials in the province was 59,400 sets, but taking into account the support of central ministries, sister provinces and municipalities, and targeted donations from all sectors of society, only 48,500 suits are available in the province, leaving a gap of nearly 11,000.

This is only a one-day gap in protective clothing in Hubei Province.

Liu Xuerong, Communist Party secretary of Huanggang, said N95 masks, medical protective clothing, goggles and other protective supplies were the most in short supply in Huanggang. In order to make up for the shortage of materials and medicines, social support is also an important channel, in addition to coordinating efforts, emergency procurement, resumption of work and production, etc. .

Private donations in action

As of February 7, the CPC Central Committee, the State Council, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, the National Development and Reform Commission and other ministries and departments, the provinces and cities (Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps) to support Hubei Province, the cumulative total of more than 10 million items of Medical Protection Materials; More than 10 million pieces of medical and protective materials were donated by various sectors of society.

Behind these 10 million pieces of social donations are tens of thousands of individuals and groups linked by industry, region, and school. They have created a protective net for front line health care workers, sending supplies from home and abroad amid a global shortage of protective materials, restrictions on overseas exports and poor logistics, according to the Split Second.

On New Year's Eve, Hubei Native Zhang Ke (not his real name) quarantined himself in Bangkok. He was in Thailand to participate in training courses, learned that the new coronavirus can be human-to-human transmission, canceled the plan to return to the country, "for fear of infecting others. ".

Zhang Ke watched the spring festival gala while brushing his friends' circle. He saw the full-screen announcement of the shortage of materials in Wuhan Hospital. He cried urgently. "The soldiers in the war don't even have weapons. They can't even protect themselves. How can they protect others? "

He saw the home can not buy everywhere mask, thinking of someone from Thailand to purchase, send back to Hubei Line. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Zhang found a girl on Weibo to run an errand, bought 20 boxes of masks, and contacted the fashion blogger CK, who was returning from Thailand, to give the masks to her to bring back. Though unable to move freely, he was relieved to be able to "do something for his compatriots in the besieged city" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Bangkok's self-isolated Zhang Ke, Weibo looks for Chinese to buy masks and send them back to the front line of Hubei

"It may be a drop in the bucket for domestic help, but I think I can help a doctor just one more day! " Zhang wrote in his diary.

He began to study a variety of medical masks, European Standard, American standard, various models and sterilization process, in the volunteer group to help alumni, foundations and other investors find, compare prices, check certificate.

The first thing he does when he wakes up in isolation is touch his forehead, swallow, confirm that he has no symptoms, and then grab his phone and get back to work.

Halfway around the world, a phd student in the UK named Yi Wei Mi (not her real name) has been losing sleep over the disease. As she scoured the news of the outbreak and scoured the world for supplies, she even had an asthma attack during her most exhausting and sad days. "I have a typical stress reaction, " she jokingly told China News Weekly. "I feel sick all over if I don't help. ".

As early as January 23, she bought 3,000 masks, more than 200 pairs of goggles and 200 sets of protective clothing from a British hygiene website. Customs clearance is slow because Chinese people around the world are moving goods and materials to China. She thought that small packages could be sent without customs clearance, so she combined masks, goggles and protective clothing into small express packages, which were airlifted to the Guangzhou Port through the Chinese logistics company, and then sent to Hubei by a relay of volunteers from Guangzhou. By her calculations, it would be a week faster than the bulk shipment.

However, as more and more Chinese are snapping up medical supplies, British sellers are sitting on their hands. As medical surgical masks have grown from # 5.50 to # 35, EMMI has been unable to cope. Her best friend's father, a doctor in Wuhan, has been battling the coronavirus for the better part of a month. According to her understanding of the situation, Wuhan designated hospitals are still very short of supplies, "every day. ".

On January 31st the BBC announced that it had confirmed two cases of COVID-19 in the UK. Message Out, easy microns have been ordered masks, protective clothing orders were canceled one after another. This is not an isolated case, many Chinese buyers in the volunteer group said they placed orders in Spain, Germany also have no reason to refund. She suspects that these countries may also be stockpiling protective gear for the outbreak.

Then look further afield, she wrote in a friend's circle, "anyone who speaks Greek, Finnish, or Estonian, please contact the dealer to find the goods, thanks! "

Interview a Xin (not his real name) , he was pulling a truck of protective materials to the Paris-Charles de Gaulle Airport. A Xin is a native of Wuhan and the Head of Manchester Premier League logistics. The supplies in his car, donated by the Chinese students'organization, were supposed to be sent from London, but the shipping space in Britain had to wait, so he immediately drove from Manchester to Paris for delivery.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to get the supplies on the plane as soon as possible, Arxin drove from Manchester to Paris

He said anxiously, at the moment, his family and high school students are fighting the virus in Wuhan, "National Crisis, I can not wait. ".

At present, overseas Chinese, alumni associations and local governments are all buying protection materials in Europe, which not only leads to higher prices for protection, but also indirectly raises the cargo space for flights to China, "increasing the price by more than 20 times per kilogram. ". But to support Wuhan, he resisted pressure to send all relief supplies to Hubei free of postage.

At present, a XIN personal donations of materials plus help Chinese prepaid freight has more than 700,000 yuan, he said with a smile actually also love money, "but now is not the time to make money. ".

In a tough situation, there's not much you can do

It is not easy for the unarmed man to deliver protection to the eye of the storm. Raise funds, find goods, open logistics, each link is like to break customs.

With 890,000 followers, the blogger CK took her family to Bangkok for the Spring Festival. When she saw the news from Wuhan that there was a material emergency, she paused her original trip and went straight to the drugstore to shop.

Ran Empty a few pharmacies to find 200 bags of N95 masks, CK rushed to take photos to send a doctor of the student qualifications. A Hong Kong couple stood next to her as she anxiously waited for confirmation. C.K. figured they were waiting for her to drop the purchase and take over.

No, and when she checked out, they said they were worried she wouldn't be able to carry all that stuff, so they helped her carry the six-pack of face masks back to the hotel.

At first, her parents didn't understand the shopping. "How much can you help? "

"If everyone thinks that, wouldn't it be worse if no one helped? " She retorted, documenting the purchase in hopes of encouraging overseas tourists to bring the masks home and "ants move" to support the front line.

"Most of them are not on the road for themselves. I suddenly find that I can't seem to stop working. ".

CK started looking for overseas distributors and eventually snapped up 12,000 N95 masks from India. It is not an exaggeration to say that a large number of Chinese in India orders of protective supplies, almost sold out the stock of pharmacies. She used her reputation as a guarantee, in two hours to raise funds, ask two volunteers to bring home the mask.

But as the Lunar New Year holiday ends and Chinese vacationers return home, it is becoming increasingly difficult to find volunteers to bring supplies home.

At the same time, the number of confirmed cases outside China also affects the export policies of the governments of other countries. India will temporarily ban exports of face masks, protective clothing and other protective equipment as a result of the new crown pneumonia outbreak, the country's foreign trade authority announced in official website on January 31. The day before, India had its first confirmed case of a new coronavirus.

Calvin Klein couldn't help but worry, the volunteers had planned to pull the next day 7,400 N95 masks from New Delhi to fly to Guangzhou, in case luggage check how to do? Equally anxious is the film "I am not a medicine God" based on Mr. Lu Yong, who in India has been ordered a considerable number of 3m masks, is planning to ship back to China.

In order to avoid being intercepted by Indian customs, he posted a request for help on Weibo, hoping that passengers returning to Kunming from New Delhi would each help bring some surgical masks home, and someone would pick up the goods when they landed. Lu also promised 10 face masks to each of the passengers who helped.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lu Yong finds Chinese tourists to bring back masks from New Delhi. Photo: Weibo@lu Yong

In addition to India, Thailand, Vietnam also announced the export of face masks related control news. Overseas defense materials procurement is faced with money can not buy goods, there is no ability to ship back to the situation.

On the other hand, the various departments frequently issued regulations on private donations of medical supplies, but also make volunteers some confusion. At the end of January, the first-line hospitals again exposed the shortage of information, triggering public questions about the Red Cross distribution of materials efficiency. After that, whether or not to bypass the Red Cross and donate directly to the hospital became the volunteers'biggest concern.

According to the official announcement on the website of the Hubei Red Cross Society, the Hubei Red Cross Society receives materials related to epidemic prevention and control according to certain standards. Donors are required to fill out a letter of intent to donate and receive verification of product qualification documents. If the intention to donate is a targeted donation, by the donor and the recipient unit butt joint, direct delivery to the recipient unit.

On February 7, the Wuhan Market Supervision Authority issued a document, appealing to the caring people "to make donations through the Red Cross as a whole as far as possible, so as not to bypass the Red Cross targeted donations and increase the burden of hospital inspection" , "All suspected violations of the law and regulations will be dealt with in accordance with the law, " he said

As soon as the news broke, it sent shockwaves through volunteers -- as many feared it would mean no more direct donations to hospitals.

Zhang, the volunteer, has his own views on the Wuhan market regulator's concerns about "increasing the burden of hospital inspections" . He said that the general public does not have enough experience in identifying the complicated medical materials, but now many volunteers have joined the medical staff and can guide people online in purchasing compliant materials, "We are very organized and we are not fighting a war. ".

On the same day, Vice Minister of Finance Yu Weiping said at a press conference that all sectors of society should be encouraged to donate to ease the pressure on medical supplies and allow direct donations to hospitals.

The Emergency Support Team of the Wuhan New Pneumonia Prevention and Control Command issued a notice on matters relating to the procurement or donation of medical supplies for epidemic prevention, which detailed the qualification requirements for medical supplies donated by the community.

Among them, domestic protection products, medical devices to provide registration and production of medical devices license. Overseas protective products need to provide overseas medical device listing documents and inspection reports.

However, from a practical point of view, volunteers in overseas procurement found that most foreign protection sellers can not provide timely or not willing to provide complete documentation. In addition, the quality monitoring system of different countries, medical protection materials in Europe, the United States, Korea and other implementation standards, how to respond to the national standard is a difficult problem.

In order to avoid the risk, some non-governmental organizations choose to donate materials to the community, streets, police and other groups with incomplete documents, but certified by professionals as conforming materials.

In fact, due to the shortage of protective materials, some protective clothing equipment allocated to the front-line medical staff of Wuhan Designated Hospital is not up to standard. Doctors at the Wuhan Central Hospital and Wuhan No. 1 Hospital told reporters that when supplies were at their most scarce, the protective clothing they were given would be easily broken in a big movement, and medical staff would "patch" the damaged protective clothing, tape continues to be used.

Volunteer Zhang Ke believes that the flow of non-compliant medical supplies to the front line, may cause potential harm to medical staff, is indeed a good intention to do bad things "suspected illegal" behavior. However, in the case of an objective material gap, Zhang Ke hopes that the regulatory authorities will give more encouragement and guidance to social donations, "professionals can be solicited from the community to help receive supplies in hospitals, or open some of the official material identification group, through the online guidance of procurement compliance materials. ".
